@Dman979 : Yep i spend a half day on the stock & another half day on BD-Armory version . i Spend the necessary time to make it flight well . Lot of tilt , rotate , flight test ... 

@KotDemopan : "Although the Cockpit pointing a bit downwards on your Mirage can be a bit disorientating on the Navball...."

Yep , but except for doing maneuver node , it isn't really needed on a plane . I use this cockpit tilt to keep level flight on a ground cruise target flight ( SAS ON on target ) without finish into water ![:)](//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif)

Have a nice day !
